  "markup": "\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPurpose:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E To encourage continuous educational development that benefits both employees and Neumo by providing tuition reimbursement for enhancing skills and knowledge for current positions or future advancements within the Company.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcedure:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Col start=\u00221\u0022 type=\u00221\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEligibility:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E To be eligible for tuition reimbursement, an employee must be a regular full-time employee and have completed at least [e.g., one year] of continuous active employment with Neumo. Reimbursement is available for associate, bachelor, and master degree programs directly related to your current position or demonstrable career advancement within the Company. We have sole discretion to determine course relevance. This may include courses leading to professional certifications directly applicable to your role. Courses must be taken at an accredited educational institution. Employees must maintain a minimum grade of [e.g., C for undergraduate, B for graduate] or a passing grade for pass/fail courses/certifications.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReimbursement Amount:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E The maximum reimbursement amount is \u003Cstrong\u003Eup to $2,000 per calendar year\u003C/strong\u003E per eligible employee. Reimbursement covers tuition costs and mandatory fees. It does not cover books, supplies, travel, living expenses, or non-mandatory fees. Reimbursement is typically provided upon successful completion of the course and submission of all required documentation.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EApplication Process:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Employees must obtain prior written approval from their immediate supervisor and Human Resources \u003Cem\u003Ebefore\u003C/em\u003E enrolling in a course for which they intend to seek reimbursement. The application for approval must include details about the course, institution, cost, and how it relates to your job or career path at Neumo.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOther Funds:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Any grants, scholarships, federal financial aid, or other tuition funds received from sources external to Neumo must be disclosed and will reduce the amount of reimbursement provided by the Company. The total reimbursement from all sources cannot exceed the actual cost of tuition and mandatory fees.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERepayment Obligation:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E If an employee voluntarily resigns from employment with Neumo within \u003Cstrong\u003Eone (1) year\u003C/strong\u003E of receiving a tuition reimbursement payment, the employee will be required to repay the \u003Cstrong\u003Efull amount\u003C/strong\u003E of the reimbursement to the Company. The reimbursed amount may be deducted from the employee\u2019s final paychecks to the extent permitted by law. Any balance that may be due after the deduction from the final paycheck must be paid by the employee within 30 calendar days from the date of termination. \u003Cstrong\u003EException:\u003C/strong\u003E If an employee is laid off due to business conditions of which the employee has no control, the employee maintains eligibility for reimbursement upon completion of the course, as long as the course began prior to the employee receiving notification of layoff or termination.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELimitations:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Approval of a course of study for tuition reimbursement, or receipt of tuition reimbursement funds, in no way obligates Neumo to change an employee\u2019s job description or work assignment, provide future salary adjustments, or extend promotions within the organization. This program is not intended to fund degrees that lead to employment outside of Neumo\u2019s core business without prior discussion and approval.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProgram Discretion:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: \u0027Times New Roman\u0027; mso-bidi-font-family: \u0027Times New Roman\u0027; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\u0022\u003E Continuation of the Tuition Reimbursement Program is at the sole discretion of Neumo. The Human Resources department will recommend a monetary amount to be allocated annually towards the tuition reimbursement benefit, dependent upon funds available. Neumo expects to maintain this program but reserves the right to alter, amend, or revoke the plan in whole or in part at any time. Any change or discontinuance will not adversely affect approved applications for the semester in which the change is made.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E"
}]]></Value>
